search:Testing Strategies for Next.js +.content:
- Install dependencies: `npm i -D vitest @testing-library/react @testing-library/jest-dom`
- Configure Jest in your project:
  ```json
  {
    "testEnvironment": "jsdom",
    "setupFilesAfterEnv": ["@testing-library/jest-dom/extend-expect"]
  }
  ```
- Use `vitest` for running tests: `npx vitest`
- For Next.js router testing, use `jest.mock('next/router')` and mock the necessary methods.
- Example of a simple test:
  ```javascript
  import { render } from '@testing-library/react';
  import MyComponent from '../path/to/MyComponent';

  test('renders correctly', () => {
    const { getByText } = render(<MyComponent />);
    expect(getByText(/example text/i)).toBeInTheDocument();
  });
  ```
- Ensure your tests are isolated and do not rely on global state.
